div.p:
The most remarkable seats of noblemen and gentlemen are, Blankney, Charles
                    Chaplin, Esq.; Brocklesby Park, Lord Yarborough; Coleby Hall, Earl Lindsey;
                    Gautby, Robert Vener, Esq.; Grinsthorpe Castle, Lord Gwydir; Hanby Hall, Sir
                    William Manners; Harmston, Samuel Thorold, Esq.; Hainton Park, G. Heneage, Esq.;
                    Noc-ton Park, Earl of Ripon; Belton House, Lord Brownlow; Normanby Hall, Sir J.
                    Sheffield; Reevesby Abbey, late Sir Joseph Banks; Subton, Sir Robert Heron;
                    Summer Castle, Lady Wrey; Syston, Sir John Thorold; Thur-gunby, Lord
                    Middleton.
